  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Transitional Homes through ACTED</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Affected population(s), Internally displaced persons (IDPs)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The global Red Cross network is helping families transition to safer, more secure homes. To support these efforts, the American Red Cross is partnering with a number of international non-governmental organizations to construct transitional homes, which include access to clean water and the installation of family latrines.  As part of this initiative, the Agency for Technical Cooperation and Development (ACTED) has constructed 1,706 transitional homes, 1500 latrines and 1700 rainwater harvesting systems. They will also conduct hygiene promotion and disaster risk reduction activities.</narrative>
  </description>
